parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the timing belt can cause engine damage, leading to costly repairs, and potentially leaving the driver stranded.
The failure of the engine cooling system can cause the engine to overheat, leading to engine damage, and potentially causing a fire.
symptoms: the engine cooling fan switch and relays fail

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A vehicle fire can cause damage to the vehicle and potentially harm the occupants.

symptoms: Heater core fluid bypass valve failure

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Heater Core Fluid Bypass Valve Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the heater core fluid bypass valve can cause damage to the heater core, leading to coolant leaks, overheating, and engine failure.
symptoms: Heater core fluid bypass valve failure

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Inadequate repair of the heater core recall can lead to continued defects, coolant leaks, overheating, and engine failure, which can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Heater core recall repair not completed

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The improper mounting of the ignition switch can cause the ignition feed wire to twist and rub against the steering column, leading to a short circuit and sudden loss of power while driving, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Sudden loss of power while driving

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the wiring harness can cause electrical shorts, leading to melted fuse boxes, and potentially resulting in fires or loss of critical vehicle systems.

The faulty recall work on the fuse holder for the air conditioner blower can cause the vehicle to overheat, leading to engine damage, and prevent the defroster from functioning properly, reducing visibility and increasing the risk of accidents.
Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or become difficult to shift, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: the transmission warning light is illuminated
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear
the vehicle loses power or stalls.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the shifter interlock can cause the vehicle to start in gear, leading to unexpected movement, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle starts when the shifter is in drive
the vehicle starts in gear without pressing the brake pedal
the shifter does not return to the park position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the right front axle bearing can cause the vehicle to vibrate, lose power, or become difficult to steer, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: the right front axle bearing is excessively worn or damaged.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Yellowing or degradation of headlights can reduce visibility, especially at night or in low-light conditions, increasing the risk of accidents. Overheating of headlights can cause intermittent or complete loss of light, further compromising visibility and safety.
symptoms: Yellowing or discoloration of headlight lenses
headlights flickering or going out intermittently
